FT  20 MAY 92 / Barry Reamsbottom elected general secretary of CPSA
Barry Reamsbottom was yesterday elected general secretary of the CPSA, the
biggest Civil Service union. He will take over the Pounds 43,000-a-year job
on June 1, when Mr John Ellis, general secretary since 1986, moves to head
the Council of Civil Service Unions. Mr Reamsbottom, 43, has edited the
union's newspaper for the past five years.
